Crispy Potato Meat Pie
  --Yumcult

Crust:
2.5 lbs / 1.2 kg potatoes (Yukon Gold or similar)
Olive oil (for coating)
Salt & Garlic powder
~1/4 c / 50 ml melted butter
~1 oz / 30 g grated Parmesan

Preheat oven to 400°F / 200°C. Cut potatoes in half and place in a baking dish. Coat with olive oil, season with salt & garlic powder. Mix well to coat; arrange cut-side down. Bake for 40-45 min. The potatoes are ready when a knife is easily inserted. Smash them flat into a 10" pie dish (or similar) lined with parchment paper (can grease if you don't like using parchment). Combine butter and parmesan; brush the mixture over the potato base. Put back in the oven and bak for another 15-20 min until crispy. Taste and adjust salt as preferred. 

Filling:
7 oz / 200 g mushrooms
1 onion, diced
1.1 lbs / 500 g Ground pork & beef mix
3-4 cloves of garlic, minced
2 tbsp tomato paste
1 tsp smoked paprika
1/2 tsp dried thyme
cayenne pepper, to taste
1 tbsp shoyu
1/2 tsp balsamic vinegar
1/2 tsp sugar
~3/4 cup / 200 ml hot water
Salt & pepper

Slice mushrooms, put in pan with oil and saute until golden brown.  Season with salt and pepper and set aside. Add more oil to the pan and saute onion until soft and golden, season with salt. Add meat and  break up, cooking until brown. Add garlic and cook for another min. Make a well and add tomato paste, cook for a minute, then add paprika, cayenne, and thyme. Stir and cook for another min. Add water, shoyu, basalmic, and sugar; stir well then cover and let simmer for 5-7 min until sauce thickens. Set aside until base is ready. Spread evenly over crispy potatoes.

Topping:
3.5 oz / 100 g Cheddar cheese, shredded
3.5 oz / 100 g Mozzarella cheese, shredded
Dried oregano (optional) 

Spread the cheeses evenly over the top of the filling. Add the mushrooms and sprinkle some oregano as desired. Bake for another 10-15 min. Let cool for a few mintes, then remove from pan and put on a rack to cool for another 15ish minutes. 

Slaw:
7-10 oz / 200-300 g cabbage, thinly slice
1 carrot, shredded
1 small onion, sliced (optional)
1 sweet-tart apple, chopped
3 tbsp olive oil
1 tbsp rice vinegar
1 tsp honey
1 tsp Dijon mustard
A mix of seeds and nuts (for topping)
Salt & pepper to taste

Combine oil, vinegar, honey, mustard, salt and pepper to taste. Combine the cabbage, onion, carrots, and apple and toss with the dressing. Let site for 10-15 min.  Lightly toast a mix of seeds and nuts to top the slaw with




Notes: Can swap alt veggies for the mushrooms ex. zucchini, bell peppers, etc. CAn use jarred sauce rather than making your own
